window.docContents[116].resolve({"/Basic-Types/Byte-Arrays/#zh-basictypes-bytearray-h002":{"contents":"Constructs a new empty byte array with initial capacity 0.Use ByteArray.emptyWithCapacity to create an array with a greater initial capacity.\n\nConstructs a new empty byte array with initial capacity c.\n\nAppends two byte arrays.In compiled code, calls to ByteArray.append are replaced with the much more efficient\nByteArray.fastAppend.\n\nAppends two byte arrays using fast array primitives instead of converting them into lists and back.In compiled code, this function replaces calls to ByteArray.append.\n\nCopies the slice at [srcOff, srcOff + len) in src to [destOff, destOff + len) in\ndest, growing dest if necessary. If exact is false, the capacity\nwill be doubled when grown.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009字节吞吐量\u0009API 参考","header":"20.17.1.1. 构造字节数组","id":"/Basic-Types/Byte-Arrays/#zh-basictypes-bytearray-h002"},"/Basic-Types/Byte-Arrays/#zh-basictypes-bytearray-h011":{"contents":"Finds the index of the first byte in a for which p returns true. If no byte\nin a satisfies p, then the result is none.The variant findFinIdx? additionally returns a proof that the found index is in bounds.\n\nFinds the index of the first byte in a for which p returns true. If no byte\nin a satisfies p, then the result is none.The index is returned along with a proof that it is a valid index in the array.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009字节吞吐量\u0009API 参考","header":"20.17.1.9. 元素谓词","id":"/Basic-Types/Byte-Arrays/#zh-basictypes-bytearray-h011"},"/Basic-Types/Strings/#zh-basictypes-string-substrings-h006":{"contents":"Returns the character at the given position in the substring.The position is relative to the substring, rather than the underlying string, and no bounds checking\nis performed with respect to the substring's end position. If the relative position is not a valid\nposition in the underlying string, the fallback value (default : Char), which is 'A', is\nreturned.  Does not panic.\n\nChecks whether a substring contains the specified character.\n\nReturns the first character in the substring.If the substring is empty, but the substring's start position is a valid position in the underlying\nstring, then the character at the start position is returned. If the substring's start position is\nnot a valid position in the string, the fallback value (default : Char), which is 'A', is\nreturned.  Does not panic.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009弦乐\u0009API 参考\u0009原始子串","header":"20.8.4.12.6. 查找","id":"/Basic-Types/Strings/#zh-basictypes-string-substrings-h006"},"/Basic-Types/Sum-Types/#sum-syntax":{"contents":"名称 Sum 和 PSum 很少明确写入。\n大多数代码使用相应的中缀运算符。\n\n\n\nSum Typesα ⊕ β 是 Sum α β 的表示法。\n\n\n\n\n\nPotentially-Propositional Sum Typesα ⊕' β 是 PSum α β 的表示法。\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009总和类型","header":"20.14.1. 句法","id":"/Basic-Types/Sum-Types/#sum-syntax"},"/Interacting-with-Lean/#format-empty":{"contents":"空字符串在 Std.Format 中没有唯一的代表。\n以下所有内容都代表空字符串：* .nil* .text \"\"* .text \"\" ++ .nil* .nil ++ .text \"\"使用 Std.Format.isEmpty 检查文档是否包含零个字符，使用 Std.Format.isNil 专门检查它是否是构造函数 Std.Format.nil。\n\nChecks whether the given format contains no characters.\n\nChecks whether a Format is the constructor Format.nil.This does not check whether the resulting rendered strings are always empty. To do that, use\nFormat.isEmpty.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009与 Lean 交互\u0009技术输出\u0009格式","header":"3.7.1.2. 空文档","id":"/Interacting-with-Lean/#format-empty"}});